HEADWORD: Thirl
<hw>Thirl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Thirled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Thirling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Thrill</er>.]</ety>
<def>To bore; to drill or thrill. See <er>Thrill</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.
or Prov.]</mark>⟦br⟧
